#: ../../A/automagically.rst:5
msgid "automagically"
msgstr "automagically"

#: ../../A/automagically.rst:7
msgid "/aw·toh·maj´i·klee/, adv\\."
msgstr "/aw·toh·maj´i·klee/, 副詞"

#: ../../A/automagically.rst:9
msgid ""
"Automatically, but in a way that, for some reason (typically because it is "
"too complicated, or too ugly, or perhaps even too trivial), the speaker "
"doesn't feel like explaining to you. See :ref:`magic`\\. \"The C-INTERCAL "
"compiler generates C, then automagically invokes :manpage:`cc(1)` to produce"
" an executable.\""
msgstr ""
"自動的に、ただし何らかの理由で(たいていは複雑すぎる、醜すぎる、あるいはおそらく些細すぎるという理由で)、話者がそれをあなたに説明する気になれないようなやり方で。\\"
" :ref:`magic`\\ を参照。「C-INTERCALコンパイラはCを生成し、それからautomagicallyに\\ "
":manpage:`cc(1)`\\ を呼び出して実行ファイルを作る」。"

#: ../../A/automagically.rst:13
msgid ""
"This term is quite old, going back at least to the mid-70s in jargon and "
"probably much earlier. The word ‘automagic’ occurred in advertising (for a "
"shirt-ironing gadget) as far back as the late 1940s."
msgstr ""
"この用語はかなり古く、隠語としては少なくとも70年代半ばまで、おそらくもっと前までさかのぼる。‘automagic’という語は、早くも1940年代後半には(シャツのアイロンがけ道具の)広告に現れていた。"
